Finding Beauty in Negative Space # In photography, what you leave out of the frame is often more important than what you put in.
Tip 1: The Rule of Thirds # Don’t put your subject in the middle. Let them breathe on the edges.
Tip 2: High Contrast # Black and white photography is perfect for minimalism because it strips away the distraction of color.
